More bug fixes. Hey everyone I am sorry this update has taken so long especially since there are so many bugs in version 3. Hurricane Ian significantly damaged my home office and I have been without power or internet. Anyways Starlink arrived today so updates should start consistently rolling out again. If you are one of the users who experienced data loss please follow the steps outlined here: https: support.apple.com en us HT201398 NOTE: Step 4 may itself result in new data loss so only proceed with it as a last measure. If the steps above don t resolve your issue please email support databenice.com with: 1. your device iOS versions 2. the Pencil it in! App Versions 3. A description what how much data is missing Thanks for your patience Mikey
Various bug fixes.

Text is here! Text is rich. Text is expressive. Text isn t just some afterthought it s built right into the drawing engine. Now you can type out your tasks journal entries notes and calendar events. Since text is built into the drawing engine you can use your Apple Pencil to cross out text highlight text and create notes that incorporate both text and drawing. Text is rich and supports many styling options including fonts colors strikethrough and much more.

Fixed a bug that could cause the UI to hang when adding a task while showing completed tasks. Fixed some minor settings bugs. Added sidebar to all Calendar views for easier drag and drop: When dropping into all day canvases the event or task will be scheduled for the day start time in Calendar Settings. Added ColorScheme overide in settings under Appearance Settings Added date labels to tasks can be turned off in Task Settings : gray means upcoming red means overdue green means completed and displays the date completed.

Hey everyone. This is a big update and I am sorry it has taken so long! New Drawing Engine which means all views now support zooming directly in the main interface. New UI for both the Calendar view and the Tasks view. Month view now supports drawing over events. Task view uses a more standard UI. No more ContextMenu simply tap an event or task to bring up its details. New settings for both Calendar view and Tasks view to adjust the row spacing . Fixed a bug that could cause the app to delete the main task list for users with multiple devices. If you have any bug reports or feature requests please reach out to me at support databenice.com Mikey

Fixed A rare crash when dragging and dropping a task A bug where drawing could look squised in Week view A bug where tapping the full screen button might delete the last stroke in Notes view Various navigation bugs in Notes view

Added Notebooks are here! Notebooks offer a more traditional note taking experience. Pages can either be lined or bank. Everyone gets 1 notebook and Pro Subscribers can add as many as their storage allows. Notebooks are great for things like class notes or projects. For the next few updates I will be working on stability improvements and bug fixes then I will be back to adding features. Mikey
Fixed A rare bug that could cause the app to hang and crash when editing a previously erased task. A scaling bug when editing tasks in detail mode.

Added Detail view for Tasks to support zooming. Can now edit a Reminder tapped in the Day view. Tasks are now sortable again. Fixed Improved the display of completed tasks. Can now delete empty task rows via the context menu. Fixed a bug to prevent dismissing Edit Reminder view with pending changes. Fixed a bug where Calendar Chooser whould appear empty.

Added Ability to change a todo s list using the context menu. Ability for pros to add and edit Reminders Fixed Bug where hiding completed todos was broken. Selected todo lists are now saved across app launches.

What s New: Pro Access Pros now have Reminders integration. Drag and Drop to schedule your Reminders which will appear in your calendar. Simply swipe left on the Tasks view to see Reminders. Bug Fixes: Fixing an issue with Pro Access entitlements.
Fixed a bug where Widgets wouldn t load data. Delaying access requests until they are needed rather than on App launch.
2.0.0 is here! New UI Pro Access: Custom Task Lists More coming soon!

Bug Fixes: Fixing crash when launching on some devices running iOS 13. Fixing a rare crash when syncing alarms between devices. Fixing a crash when paging in Month View during a Drag and Drop operation. Auto Zoom now zooms to today if in the current month.

Features: More Colors: Pick any color you want using Apple s Color Picker New DatePicker: Tap the Date Label once to show the DatePicker. Tap and hold the Date Label to jump to Today. Auto Zoom in Month View: Automatically zoom in when selecting a tool. Off by default can be turned on in Month Settings. Bug Fixes: Fixing a bug where white black ink would appear missing in the Widget.
Bug Fixes: Fixing a crash that could occur when paging. Fixing incorrect Day in Today s Schedule Widget.
Fixing Widget Bugs: Wrong Date in Schedule Bad alignment of Date Label

Widgets are here! See your day s schedule at a glance. Keep track of overdue todos. Todos now support alarms. Better Context Menu options for todos Drag and Drop to organizer your schedule. Drag and Drop now works across days. Simply start a drag and page to the day you want to move an event.
All Drag and Drop to schedule your day Dragging between days coming soon
